{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This family includes Coiled-coil-helix-coiled-coil-helix domain-containing protein 2 and 10 (CHCHD2/10) from human and its orthologues. CHCHD2/10 are homologous proteins that form a complex in the mitochondrial intermembrane space and cooperate to regulate mitochondrial function, playing a role in mitochondrial dynamics and cristae organisation [[cite:PUB00155328], [cite:PUB00155330]]. CHCHD2 is a transcription factor that binds to specific DNA elements and activate transcription under varying oxygen conditions, including both hypoxia and normoxia [[cite:PUB00086618], [cite:PUB00066967], [cite:PUB00155329]]. It has been reported to regulate oxidative phosphorylation (OXPHOS), promoting the expression of the COX4I2 subunit during stress, inhibiting apoptosis [[cite:PUB00155331], [cite:PUB00155330]]. CHCHD10 regulates mitochondrial COX activity and mitochondrial respiration at hypoxia [[cite:PUB00155328]]. Mutations in CHCHD2 and CHCHD10 have been identified as causing Parkinson's disease and amyotrophic lateral sclerosis/frontotemporal dementia/myopathy, respectively [[cite:PUB00155330], [cite:PUB00155332]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR13523" "COILED-COIL-HELIX-COILED-COIL-HELIX DOMAIN CONTAINING 2/NUR77"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Coiled-coil-helix-coiled-coil-helix domain-containing protein 2/10-like", "short" "CHCHD2/10-like"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 2494, "taxa" 8531, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 5410, "sets" 0, "proteins" 5410, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 3561}, "pathways" 2}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR055304", :literature {"PUB00155332" {"URL" nil, "issue" nil, "authors" ["Woo JA" "Liu T" "Trotter C" "Fang CC" "